{
  "stem": "19198.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- Hanukkah was a specially beloved holiday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And following in my grandfather's footsteps, even as a fairly small child, I started making my own set of gifts for every member of the-- of the family.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I arranged all the Hanukkah observances in my own way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They gave me a great deal of freedom and I suppose that had a great deal to do with my eventually wanting to be a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A Friday night, especially in my grandparents' home, was mainly a very important family meal, usually with a four course meal with soup and-- and meat then dessert.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If my memory serves me right, we usually, the entire family ate at my grandparents' home, rather than eating separately, which we did the rest of the week.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the men went to the synagogue, including this man, even from I suppose age three or four on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we came home for the-- for the meal and spent the rest of the evening together.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A major problem arose when I wanted to-- to join a [NON-ENGLISH], a gymnastic organization which had its annual exercises on a Friday night.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was just-- even after that my parents agreed that I could, it was emotionally very difficult for me to leave the home on Friday night.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandmother.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the first thing my-- my father and I think my grandfather blessed me and then we had the kiddish at home before the-- as we started the meal.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I started public school today age six.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
